# .cursorrules

Project: Karate Tracker — React/TypeScript family training app

Tech stack:
  - React 18, TypeScript, Vite
  - Tailwind CSS for styling
  - Local storage → Firebase (migration in progress)
  - Google Calendar API

Code standards:
  - Functional components only, no class components
  - Custom hooks for all data logic (no business logic in components)
  - Components max 150 lines; split larger ones
  - TypeScript strict mode — no 'any'
  - File naming: PascalCase for components, camelCase for hooks (useXxx)

Data model:
  - Student: { id, name, belt, birthdate, photoUrl }
  - Session: { id, date, studentId, type, duration, notes, techniquesWorkedOn }
  - Belt: { rank, color, minAge, requirements[] }

Do not suggest Redux or Zustand. Use React Context only if needed across 3+ components.
Always include loading and error states.
Write JSDoc for all hooks.